Over N1.5 million has been announced as the Hajj fare for 2019 by Nasarawa State Muslim pilgrims board. The Executive Secretary, Nasarawa State Muslim Pilgrims Welfare Board Welfare Board, (NSMPWB) Mallam Idris Ahmad Al-makura said: “The fee is N1,539,605.10″ and called on intending Pilgrims to complete their hajj fare on time to enable the board complete its preparation. “All prospective Pilgrims from the state will receive flat rate of the sum of eight hundred dollars $800 as BTA,” he added. According to him, the announcement of the final Hajj fare followed the approval by the National Hajj Commission of Nigeria and the Nasarawa State Governor Umaru Tanko Al-makura. He called on intending Pilgrims from the state to ensure that they follow due process in the payment of their hajj fare to avoid being defrauded. Hajj: Lagos intending pilgrims get April 15 payment deadline Bauchi governor approves 2015 Hajj fares JUST IN: Kaduna pilgrims board announces 2019 Hajj fare Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin